Surfer Chris Blowes is in a critical condition after being bitten by a shark at Fishery Bay in South Australia . 
  The 26-year-old was airlifted to the Royal Adelaide Hospital on Saturday morning . 
  Witnesses said the man was bitten in the thigh by a six-metre Great White shark . 
  The man was seen swimming away with his surfboard in its jaw . 
  Mr Blowes was surfing near Right Point in Port Lincoln National Park when he was attacked . 
  He has been identified as the man who was bitten by the shark . 
 